## Development principles (summary)

We follow **true Agile** (values from the Manifesto, not Scrum-by-default), **Extreme Programming**, **Lean**, and **iterative** delivery. The anchor habit is simplicity (XP rule of thumb — see [xp_simplicity_is_the_key.md](../../docs/dev/xp_simplicity_is_the_key.md)).

We strive to write tests: **Classical TDD** on the backend first ([unit_testing_strategy.md](../../docs/dev/unit_testing_strategy.md), [unit_testing_sapie.md](../../docs/dev/unit_testing_sapie.md)).
**E2E** tests exist but are **not maintained** during this MVP push unless a story explicitly requires them — see
[contributing_guidelines.md](../../docs/dev/contributing_guidelines.md).

For the full principle set and how they apply in code review,
use [development_principles.md](../../docs/dev/development_principles.md).

